article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 20, Northwestern St. 11
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Danny Southall threw for one touchdown and ran for another to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 20-11 victory over Northwestern State Thursday night. Southall completed a 19-yard touchdown pass to Dominiq Edison with 10:27 left in the first half and scored on an 11-yard run four minutes later. Cory Long scored on field goals of 28 and 21 yards in the first half to give the Lumberjacks (4-7,4-2 Southland) a 20-0 lead at the half. Robert Weeks kicked a 23-yard field goal for Northwestern State (4-7, 2-4) late in the third quarter and Dudley Guice caught a 2-yard touchdown pass from Ro Charpentier with 19 seconds left for the final score. Southall completed 10-of-22 passes for 130 yards and had one interception. He rushed for 46 yards. Jerome Brooks carried 22 times for 124 yards. Stephen F. Austin stifled Northwestern State's running game. Anton Robinson rushed for 32 yards and Charpentier had -37 yards rushing. Charpentier completed 16-of-33 passes for 148 yards and had one interception.
